        print('%s %s' %(i+1,ii+1),end='\r')
        
        if i >ii:
            densities = densCols(targets_df_only_ecaas_top5000.iloc[i], targets_df_only_ecaas_top5000.iloc[ii],nbin = 400)

            r,_ = pearsonr(targets_df_only_ecaas_top5000.iloc[i], targets_df_only_ecaas_top5000.iloc[ii])

        if i == ii :
            hist, bins = np.histogram(targets_df_only_ecaas_top5000.iloc[i], bins=100)

        if i < ii:
            axs[i,ii].set_visible(False)

from scipy.stats import pearsonr

scale = 8

            r,_ = pearsonr(targets_y_p_154.iloc[i], targets_y_p_154.iloc[ii])

        if i == ii :
